What is Cron?
Cron automates repetitive tasks.

Edit Cron Jobs:
crontab -e

View Cron Jobs:
crontab -l

Cron Format:
* * * * *
│ │ │ │ │
│ │ │ │ └── Day of Week
│ │ │ └──── Month
│ │ └────── Day
│ └──────── Hour
└────────── Minute

Examples:
Run every minute:

* * * * * /home/devops/script.sh

Run daily at midnight:

0 0 * * * /backup.sh

Run every Sunday:

0 2 * * 0 /weekly-backup.sh
Real-Time Scenario

Automated log cleanup.

0 1 * * * find /var/log -type f -mtime +30 -delete
